title: unique() and type() are not availabe in graph.nodes()
body_html:
unique() and type() functions are not available in the nodes from graph.nodes() of jit.trace. I used to fetch those before some upgrade I made recently. As @apaszke suggested, It should be present in the internal data structure but the new upgrade just removed it from python scope

for val in trace.graph().nodes():
    print(val.unique())  # doesn't have unique
    for input_node in val.inputs():
        print(input_node.unique())  # has unique
body:
``unique()`` and ``type()`` functions are not available in the nodes from ``graph.nodes()`` of ``jit.trace``. I used to fetch those before some upgrade I made recently. As @apaszke suggested, It should be present in the internal data structure but the new upgrade just removed it from python scope

```
for val in trace.graph().nodes():
    print(val.unique())  # doesn't have unique
    for input_node in val.inputs():
        print(input_node.unique())  # has unique
```
